<br>
Ok, so this good person decides to move.  S/he tells all his friends on the old server.  They talk about it, too.  Word gets around that this respected person has moved to FV.  Why?  Because of lack of contestation over raid targets due to low population.  Now the idiots all think &quot;wow, phat lewt from bazaar for me!&quot; or &quot;hey!  now I can join a raid guild cuz none of the looser guilds on my server would accept me&quot;  And, look, here they come hitting market with &quot;completely unknown person wtb raid loot, send email to ebayfool@hotmail.com&quot; or sending apps to guilds when no one knows them and they aren't even on FV yet.<br>
<br>
Eventually, when they don't get into a raiding guild (which they won't).  They'll band together out of simple frustration and whether is deliberate or just a result of the nature of the beast, that guild will be a nightmare.  The guild with the lowest entry standards is always the nightmare guild.  It happens on every single server as soon as the population gets large enough and high level enough.  It will happen on FV, too.  I see it starting to happen now just the way it happened on Tunare.  The number of (imho) undesireable high level characters on FV has shot way up VERY quickly.  Much quicker than homegrown can reasonably explain.  Eventually every server spawns a nightmare guild.  The naked transfer combined with the quick-fix gearing of zero no-drops on FV will make it happen far faster.<br>
<br>
One good direct recruit just isn't worth five indirect numbnuts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=splok>Splok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/22/03 9:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3496.topic&index=292>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The biggest problem with ..</span><hr size=1> &quot;If you stop taking these people in then you can help put pressure on Reso when they join in you can both put pressure on CT and AD. It is a house of cards and you are the Ace of Spades. <br>
